				|&lt;/form>

		h2 Card grids

		p Card grids spread a variety of rich elements in an organised grid.

		p Card containers have three preset sizes: #[code lg] will not collapse, #[code md] will collapse once (to 50% width) and #[code sm] will collapse twice (to 33% and 50% width).

		p Within cards, #[code p] elements fill the entire empty space. Apart from that, there is no predefined behaviour and you can do with them whatever you like.

		p You can add the #[code small] class to individual cards to give them small text size.

		p Any remaining cards in the last row are automatically stretched to fill the screen.

		.cards.sm
			.card
				h5 Alpha
				p This is a regular card with just text.
			.card
				h5 Beta
				p This card also has a button.
				button.primary.fill Nice button!
			.card.small
				h5 Gamma
				p This card features small text.
			.card
				h5 Delta
				p This card will fill the bottom of the screen if your viewport is large enough.

		pre(data-lang="HTML")
			code
				| &lt;div class="cards sm">
				|	&lt;div class="card">
				|		&lt;h5>Alpha&lt;/h5>
				|		&lt;p>...&lt;/p>
				|	&lt;/div>
				|	&lt;div class="card">
				|		&lt;h5>Beta&lt;/h5>
				|		&lt;p>...&lt;/p>
				|		&lt;button class="primary fill">Nice button!&lt;/button>
				|	&lt;/div>
				|	&lt;div class="card small">
				|		&lt;h5>Gamma&lt;/h5>
				|		&lt;p>...&lt;/p>
